de.fuberlin.panda.metadata.result.fusion.areal

Class GeoArea

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.fuberlin.panda.metadata.result.fusion.areal.GeoArea

  • public class GeoArea
extends java.lang.Object
    This class extends the Area class. It overrides the contains(double, double) method and adds a containsPartOf(GeoArea) method.
    Since:
    25.02.2014
    Author:
    Sebastian Schulz
    See Also:
    GeoArea(ArrayList), setBoundaryPath(), contains(double, double), containsPartOf(GeoArea)

      • GeoArea

        public GeoArea(java.util.ArrayList<java.awt.geom.Point2D.Double> boundary)
        The constructor calls the super constructor to create an empty area. Afterwards it stores the given boundary points in a private field called boundaryPoints. Subsequently they are transformed into a Path2D.Double object by calling setBoundaryPath(). Finally a new created area is added to the GeoArea. This is the actual creation of the area.
        Parameters:
        boundary - - a ArrayList of Point2D.Double which represents the boundary of the Area.

    • Method Detail

      • setBoundaryPath

        private java.awt.geom.Path2D.Double setBoundaryPath()
        This method is called by the constructor. It converts the boundaryPoints ArrayList set before into a Path2D.Double object.
        Returns:
        a Path2D.Double object.

      • contains

        public boolean contains(double x,
               double y)
        This method overrides the contains(double, double) method because of the insideness. In this case every point on the boundary is inside the polygon.

      • containsPartOf

        public boolean containsPartOf(GeoArea secondArea)
        This method checks if a boundary point of a second area is contained in the current GeoArea.
        Parameters:
        secondArea - - a GeoArea object.
        Returns:
        a boolean value.

      • add

        public void add(GeoArea geoArea)
        This method checks if the boundary points of the given GeoArea are not contained in the local GeoArea and adds them to the local boundaryPoints. Finally the given area is added to the local area.
        Parameters:
        geoArea - - a GeoArea object.
